  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2017 2018 Single grant: Sudanese Crisis - Response in Chad</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective is to contribute to the local integration of Sudanese refugees from the Mil&#xE9; and Kounoungou camps into 22 neighbouring villages of the Dar Tama Department, Wadi Fira Region in Eastern Chad through support to refugees and host population to strengthen their self-reliance and social cohesion</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project applies a holistic approach to food security, ensuring interventions via multiple sectors and thereby increases the chances for self-reliance. It is based on an approach seeking to link the following three elements; Emergency interventions such as distribution to Sudanese refugees of agricultural inputs (seeds, tools and capacity development) to increase and vary food production, and construction of wells and latrines to ensure access to water and sanitation. Assistance to host communities who will be included into the agricultural activities as well as WASH activities. These interventions not only respond to fundamental needs but also strengthen coexistence and prevent conflicts between refugees and host populations. Long-term interventions in the support of local development plans, including support to agro-forestry-pastoral activities, establishment of cereal banks and livestock farming. 4% of the budget is earmarked for partner&apos;s administration costs.</narrative>
  </description>
